%I A349418 #28 May 30 2026 14:34:24
%S A349418 16,28,46,71,104,146,198,261,336,424,526,643,776,926,1094,1281,1488,
%T A349418 1716,1966,2239,2536,2858,3206,3581,3984,4416,4878,5371,5896,6454,
%U A349418 7046,7673,8336,9036,9774,10551,11368,12226,13126,14069,15056,16088,17166,18291,19464,20686
%N A349418 a(n) is the Wiener index of a tridon on n vertices.
%C A349418 A tridon on n vertices is a caterpillar that is obtained by adding 2 distinct pendant vertices to the first (or last) internal vertex of a path on n >= 3 vertices.
%H A349418 <a href="/index/Rec#order_04">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (4,-6,4,-1).
%F A349418 a(n) = (1/6)*n^3 - (19/6)*n + 11.
%F A349418 From _Elmo R. Oliveira_, May 30 2026: (Start)
%F A349418 G.f.: x^5*(4 - 3*x)*(4 - 6*x + 3*x^2)/(1 - x)^4.
%F A349418 a(n) = 4*a(n-1) - 6*a(n-2) + 4*a(n-3) - a(n-4) for n > 8.
%F A349418 E.g.f.: (1/24)*(exp(x)*(264 - 72*x + 12*x^2 + 4*x^3) - (264 + 192*x + 72*x^2 + 24*x^3 + 9*x^4)). (End)
%e A349418 For n=5, a(5)=16 gives the Wiener index of a star graph on 5 vertices. Also, for n=6, a(6)=28 gives the Wiener index of a tridon graph on 6 vertices.
